article.headline: Hofstra 38, Rhode Island 24
article.story:
SOUTH KINGSTOWN, R.I. (AP) -- Anton Clarkson passed for 415 yards
and ran for a touchdown as Hofstra beat Rhode Island 38-24 on
Saturday.

Clarkson completed 29 of 36 passes for Hofstra (5-3, 3-2 A10).
Devale Ellis caught 11 passes for 138 yards and wideout Charles
Sullivan added 116 yards on five receptions.

After Hofstra fumbled on the opening kickoff, Rhode Island (4-5,
2-4) scored first on Brian Giannecchini's 35-yard field goal,
making the score 3-0.

The Pride drew even at 3-3 with 9:45 remaining in the first half
with Rob Zarrilli's 18-yard field goal.

Kareem Huggins, who scored twice and ran for 91 yards, put
Hofstra ahead 10-3 with 1:48 left in the first half with a 12-yard
rush, capping Hofstra's 11-play, 79-yard drive. Hofstra kept the
10-3 lead at halftime.

Clarkson's 3-yard touchdown run late in the third quarter put
Hofstra ahead 31-10.

Joe Casey carried 28 times for 170 yards for Rhode Island.
Quarterback Jayson Davis rushed for 102 yards on 21 carries for the
Rams, who rushed for 334 yards.
